{
  "stem": "22869.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They came running every day to the window there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They couldn't come in because it was all gated up.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they begged me I should get out there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I really felt so miserable.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was, like, thankful to God that I can have a little rest there, then I have to go to work.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It sounded-- it sounded-- you know, it sounds funny right now, but to get a little relief of not having to go to work, and I got at least my cup of coffee in the morning and a piece of bread, that it was like the whole-- a whole new world opened up for me.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Except the danger that my brothers knew is that every time that this placed filled up, which took maybe-- I don't know, 1,000 maybe 1,500 people-- they used to come with big vans, and they used to load all these people up, and they used to take them to the crematorium to gas them and get rid of them.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was-- I was too stupid at that time or losing my mind even to think of such a thing and probably so degraded by now in so far not caring that it just-- it just didn't matter.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Probably the same way as the other guy had the stamina to run to the wires and take his life, that was my was of saying, enough is enough.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I can't do it anymore.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then one day, they were emptying out that infirmary.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And everybody had to go to the yard outside.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Of course, that was the day that they were going to get rid of them.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So as everybody walked out, there were two guys, also people who were from the concentration camp, asking you what's the matter with you.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
